document.title: Ohio's Early Learning and Development Standards

A784911EEB6F4141A9C247848FB678E7.description:
With modeling and support,
explore a variety of digital tools
to express ideas.

3D3F3CA02091401A93FA14792BE4C890.description:
With modeling and support,
participate in shared research and
writing projects using a variety of
resources to gather information or to
answer a question.

2722C8730568401FA9273CA023ABAF0D.description:
With modeling and support, discuss
and respond to questions from others
about writing/drawing.

2403905E94874A92B9A404B2F1BB2F9B.description:
With modeling and support, use a
combination of drawing, dictating and
emergent writing to tell a story, to express
ideas, and to share information about an
experience or topic of interest. (Composition)

A40E8080C120417E90C1522E25D30049.description:
With modeling and support, use a combination
of drawing, dictating and emergent writing
for a variety of purposes (e.g., letters, greeting
cards, menus, lists, books).

4F2A4B77F71845788DD137946C7A1953.description:
With modeling and support, notice
and sporadically use punctuation
in writing.

9EC572C75302463A8E5CFD8254597D29.description:
With modeling and support, show
awareness that one letter or cluster of
letters represents one word.

869FC7401D0B4F85877A31E055D16C2E.description:
With modeling and support, demonstrate
letter formation in “writing.”

DAB9A14BE6DB43BD9F0356BBA9728552.description:
With modeling and support, print letters
of own name and other meaningful words
with mock letters and some actual letters.

17706A9C3CE546B7B7C820581D397C38.description:
Demonstrate an understanding of
the structure and function of print.

0E25DAB1C4074B97B94FC779981E42A5.description:
Use a 3-finger grasp of dominant
hand to hold a writing tool.

99ACEFBFDA1D4C05B7136ED9744AF1F5.description:
With modeling and support, recognize
the sounds associated with letters.

C404621F61164767AD4B50778FACD4B3.description:
With modeling and support, demonstrate
understanding that alphabet letters are a
special category of symbols that can be
named and identified.

D84838E5E26444F396043894DE31B4DD.description:
With modeling and support,
recognize and name some upper
and lower case letters in addition
to those in first name.

6ADD2C7A8CF445739290BB68E33ED72B.description:
With modeling and support,
recognize and “read” familiar
words or environmental print

8F9BA58FE13746FAADF14802272E5B42.description:
With modeling and support
identify initial and final sounds
in spoken words.

3D6C6CFA66324F12B8A4D1B95DBBB8DC.description:
With modeling and support, blend
and segment onset and rhyme in
single-syllable spoken words.

FEB4AD5F00F4403A8D06E539A9990CD0.description:
With modeling and support,
orally blend and segment familiar
compound words.

F424BEC46FB144C3B3AEE9913E09CAA0.description:
With modeling and support identify,
blend and segment syllables in
spoken words.

D71E99D18F164C0F8053065746BB3350.description:
With modeling and support, recognize
words in spoken sentences.

A369FE2AB76340C6B4D839B3D1052226.description:
With modeling and support, recognize
and produce rhyming words.

7A9A2C1A20074F2088BD4DB2390507EA.description:
Demonstrate an understanding that
print carries meaning.

1C1E34613DE1467CA252F1DC1363D1CE.description:
Orient books correctly for reading
and turn pages one at a time.

AD36CD22281C4AA28AA867004ECB50CE.description:
Demonstrate an understanding of
basic conventions of print in English
and other languages

C068F164609F450BA949BB6BD7BACCC4.description:
With modeling and support use
phrasing, intonation and expression
in shared reading of familiar books,
poems, chants, songs, nursery
rhymes or other repetitious or
predictable texts.

D46240B5329D464DB9514D3D2F0BDC7D.description:
Actively engage in group reading with
purpose and understanding.

3B58ABEF01214D58B2342E0AA2319BF7.description:
With modeling and support, discuss
some similarities and differences
between two texts on the same topic
(e.g., illustrations, descriptions).

09D6BC368A954D07937EE2367A48EDB4.description:
With modeling and support,
describe, categorize and compare
and contrast information in
informational text.

F26230C5F9A4462BB6FAA515B6402FE3.description:
With modeling and support,
identify the topic of an
informational text that has
been read aloud.

9A05C3FAC9F24D62B8060DDCFF9686FD.description:
With modeling and support,
name the author and illustrator
of a story and what part each
person does for a book.

F47FC528495240CE8B00A07783F840A7.description:
With modeling and support,
describe what part of the story
the illustration depicts.

EEF7AA1EB6B14DE997023E44FF6B03F4.description:
Demonstrate an understanding of
the differences between fantasy
and reality.

846D16648E6E45D599F56F2BE0D2B41A.description:
Identify characters and major
events in a story.

507ED47C0F9E485A91556675F8D8B726.description:
Ask and answer questions, and
comment about characters and
major events in familiar stories.

D0A6B3F29B2D49B98FED3E0CFA0B7C2C.description:
With modeling and support,
continue a conversation through
multiple exchanges.

8E4FEB91445E4BA9A89885E461E52BC4.description:
With modeling and support,
follow typical patterns when
communicating with others (e.g.,
listen to others, take turns talking
and speaking about the topic or
text being discussed).

9184BD162F9A4ED69984DC17BE909B6B.description:
With modeling and support,
explore relationships between word
meanings (e.g., categories of objects,
opposites, verbs describing similar
actions - walk, march, prance, etc.).
(Vocabulary)

0AA8F301A15F4E269FEB0A43B88A0E83.description:
Identify real-life connections between
words and their use. (Vocabulary)

05C354AC71FF4353ADA8841335E049FE.description:
With modeling and support,
determine the meanings of unknown
words/concepts using the context
of conversations, pictures that
accompany text or concrete objects.
(Vocabulary)

3D80C0C39B5C47B1B0618DFBD321EE7E.description:
With modeling and support, use words
acquired through conversations and shared
reading experiences. (Vocabulary)

CE7A8BCFFFB04E5FAAE205FE5EF1ADA3.description:
Produce and expand complete sentences
in shared language activities.

71210F46740E4B8DBDD4D00339711909.description:
Use frequently occurring prepositions
(e.g., to, from, in, out, on, off, for, of,
by, with).

AA54AEEFEC744E878909D584D3CDCFE9.description:
Understand and use question words
(interrogatives) (e.g., who, what, where,
when, why, how).

398348BC7DB44E628667EDE75791CAAE.description:
Form regular plural nouns orally by
adding /s/ or /es/.

7F896264DBFD498E9F45E19485DE5C68.description:
Use familiar nouns and verbs to
describe persons, animals, places,
events, actions, etc.

EEEE33F2028241F7B5B3135C25B92787.description:
With modeling and support, use the
conventions of standard English. (Grammar)

48D8FDB56911403EA2E7A12B315EA58F.description:
Use drawings or other visuals to
add details to verbal descriptions

38CD1E6B4E6D455086FED7FFA9E353BE.description:
Describe familiar people, places,
things and experiences.

DAF32687ACF64496B32C67E576E37095.description:
Speak audibly and express
thoughts, feelings and ideas
clearly. (Articulation)

B48B292ED94745E7891FE3DCCDF16DAD.description:
Use language to communicate in
a variety of ways with others to
share observations, ideas and
experiences; problem-solve, reason,
predict and seek new information.

8D6FC09DCA314650A255AD23F5A4307C.description:
Demonstrate understanding
of increasingly complex concepts
and longer sentences.

BD38D40F3F5846A8B1D4E68ECE07218A.description:
With modeling and support,
recognize similarities and
differences between people and
other living things.

955AF57751EB44F18BC0EC13775E49E6.description:
With modeling and support,
demonstrate an understanding
that living things change over
time (e.g., life cycle).

6154EC06E1974F2C8FA0AEFAF20A3CC5.description:
With modeling and support,
demonstrate knowledge of body
parts and bodily processes (e.g.,
eating, sleeping, breathing,
walking) in humans and
other animals.

8D9528B1D9F94A58AA2CF8B6DE9744D0.description:
With modeling and support,
identify and explore the
relationship between living things
and their environments (e.g.,
habitats, food, eating habits, etc.).

4559D8A54B374A5EBFD4B1ABB2E96B47.description:
With modeling and support,
identify physical characteristics and
simple behaviors of living things

57029AA4CAEA4AD9925ACD8E3DB8575F.description:
With modeling and support,
explore the properties and
characteristics of sound and light.

2467C7C2909C491D9FBC7DB139A11B72.description:
With modeling and support,
explore the position and motion
of objects.

83C8E647781140B3882F9D771FB7FEBF.description:
With modeling and support,
explore the properties of objects
and materials (e.g., solids
and liquids).

7C80DC4A6C8249AEA79C244E5468CAF7.description:
With modeling and support,
develop understanding of the
relationship between humans
and nature; recognizing the
difference between helpful and
harmful actions toward the
natural environment.

5BF06D75BF6B4D6A9C3D6D3CB07D2C71.description:
With modeling and support,
recognize familiar elements of
the natural environment and
understand that these may change
over time (e.g., soil, weather, sun
and moon).

39EACD8CFB3548B68FA377E019C2DCAD.description:
Share findings, ideas and
explanations (may be correct
or incorrect) through a variety
of methods (e.g., pictures,
words, dramatization).

6D39C0800F2C459E8426E3DD2FD9742F.description:
Make inferences, generalizations
and explanations based on
evidence.

ABE7E8569C674BD5958B253D78AE89CE.description:
Use simple tools to extend
investigation.

2793749B03704689989EB559F83BF4F3.description:
Record observations using words,
pictures, charts, graphs, etc.

C1C1E284379A4692A881E964DD0B6704.description:
Describe, compare, sort, classify,
and order.

97394FF2D4D94A28A279D53E19D47869.description:
Pose questions about the physical
and natural environment.

912593EF9E3D4EFFA952D2FE85307940.description:
Explore objects, materials and events in
the environment.

AE4BF22C2CA74634B16C4D9966F11BBA.description:
With modeling and support, demonstrate
responsible consumption and conservation
of resources.

17858037923143CC959B236A9054AABD.description:
With modeling and support, demonstrate
understanding of where goods and services
originate and how they are acquired.

D2A627AA3C294E2CBE7C07F7BA6AF7DA.description:
With modeling and support, recognize that
people have wants and must make choices
to satisfy those wants because resources
and materials are limited.

CD82FD2DEA1842D894573DB578AC3AA0.description:
With modeling and support, demonstrate
understanding that rules play an important
role in promoting safety and protecting
fairness.

5A103974F55F480385F32A1E164797DD.description:
With modeling and support, demonstrate
an awareness of the outcomes of choices.

30ECD09B33AD4A2CB450F47133E4DC9D.description:
With modeling and support, negotiate to
solve social conflicts with peers.

EF3972051FF949A999E06C70EE11B71B.description:
Demonstrate cooperative behaviors and
fairness in social interactions.

B35089B0DAEC4573B28CD73BFA92721C.description:
Understand that everyone has rights and
responsibilities within a group.

5BD4F099066B47E0B5A03A93F73282DF.description:
Identify similarities and differences of
personal, family and cultural characteristics,
and those of others.

1DF41D1CE85D4F5B833D119E5B2725ED.description:
Demonstrate a beginning understanding of
maps as actual representations of places.

26B99D75F7C343AD982A8AD93133D788.description:
Develop an awareness and appreciation of
family cultural stories and traditions.

3580EC5308A146A8819CD15E58F793F9.description:
Develop an awareness of his/her personal
history.

035B88B1C6F04EC9BB7FB2D17F8869AB.description:
Demonstrate an understanding
of time in the context of
daily experiences

B355D494DE704759A43E856F80AA4734.description: Cognition and General Knowledge: Social Studies

D763623702D6430FBF4832F4E2F8613F.description:
Combine simple shapes to form
larger shapes.

32DEF2677D1547F1AAE0553784E985B6.description:
Create shapes during play by
building, drawing, etc.

1D6A8EE7598D4ACC87D6208805E12995.description:
Compare two-dimensional shapes,
in different sizes and orientations,
using informal language

9FC7DE2EA61C4DF29B2865916E96F6D1.description:
Name three-dimensional objects
using informal, descriptive
vocabulary (e.g., “cube” for box,
“ice cream cone” for cone, “ball”
for sphere, etc.).

8A04468F1FD24455BCC0D87B845625A2.description:
Understand and use names of
shapes when identifying objects

E2E2257D25C94449ABBE40563683CCF6.description:
Demonstrate understanding of
the relative position of objects
using terms such as in/on/under,
up/down, inside/outside, above/
below, beside/between, in front of/
behind and next to.

E9592D26BB074CE091A35E046ED82201.description:
Collect data by categories to
answer simple questions.

A85EB89E981C4C0C868F5995D472ABFB.description:
Measure length and volume
(capacity) using non-standard or
standard measurement tools.

195DF68C1FD4431D9B8F40A0BDC62240.description:
Order objects by measurable
attribute (e.g., biggest to
smallest, etc.).

96586903E3824D6AB22C12F9D802FD9A.description:
Recognize, duplicate and extend
simple patterns using attributes
such as color, shape or size.

96CAA4B169B34B1D9301B5CBCE51396B.description:
Sort and classify objects by one or
more attributes (e.g., size, number).

6A90006BD1F24E8A8FE489D09301605C.description:
Count to solve simple addition
and subtraction problems with
totals smaller than 8, using
concrete objects.

BE7E4378D2A44D18B096E92099828496.description:
Identify whether the number of
objects in one group is greater
than, less than or equal to the
number of objects in another
group up to 10.

767356F839FC4820B83204BA218C3B2A.description:
Understand that the last number
spoken tells the number of
objects counted.

D5FDC3174FFC4969807F1EF471E465CC.description:
Demonstrate one-to-one
correspondence when counting
objects up to 10.

056E641206464A1B9B4DBFCB6385070D.description:
Identify without counting
small quantities of up to 3
items. (Subsidize)

81939A45691E4E18B72662593AE449B8.description:
Count to 20 by ones with
increasing accuracy.

D5223847E67A4824A073AFDF65528A41.description:
Explain reasoning for the
solution selected.

AF6F401C03E14A4A86E532BD35CEEE86.description:
Seek more than one solution to a
question, problem or task.

6A6E79AD3DEF421692A2DC8AE6D70ED3.description:
Solve problems by planning and
carrying out a sequence of actions.

32B46C43B39D409B96BC006D70901AB4.description:
Demonstrate ability to solve
everyday problems based upon
past experience.

C479224ED8A14C64901CEA2F9B7843F2.description:
Participate cooperatively in
complex pretend play, involving
assigned roles and an overall plan.

02EE3B4532E4453699CBEC0AF8D99EDE.description:
Demonstrate understanding that
symbols carry meaning and use
symbols to represent thinking
(e.g., drawings, construction
or movement).

40291DF7BB2841648E15A8AE18D0CFF8.description:
Recreate complex ideas, events/
situations with personal adaptations.

66934A1D07BE42C689151C67143B78E9.description:
With modeling and support,
remember and use information
for a variety of purposes.

A0C86F87553D4B2C9B565AF0EE594ED4.description:
Communicate about past
events and anticipate what
comes next during familiar
routines and experiences

999E06A63E23463796C487F33B9C7D42.description:
With modeling and support, demonstrate ability to
follow transportation and pedestrian safety rules.

D12DBCAE82E341F2963E652851BEE991.description:
With modeling and support, demonstrate ability
to follow emergency routines (e.g., fire or
tornado drill).

D6DE8F624D2445E996933D5EB5AE54D0.description:
With modeling and support, identify the
consequences of unsafe behavior.

E531F1A13DA649618F353391C0867AAF.description:
Identify ways adults help to keep
us safe.

A4015FDB5C424DEB807151945870FBE5.description:
With modeling and support,
identify and follow basic
safety rules.

E85F185F37F34C4BAE9F4857056F8C0D.description:
Independently complete personal
care tasks (e.g., toileting, teethbrushing,
hand-washing, dressing
etc.).

7156BF5B10BE49CD9FC953B3478775EA.description:
Demonstrate basic understanding
that eating a variety of foods helps
the body grow and be healthy.

9F18D1258A5B4FE9905532B97250B5FD.description:
Demonstrate basic understanding
that physical activity helps the
body grow and be healthy.

E34F5369ADA14DE7A94602BEB3BE7ADA.description:
Participate in structured and
unstructured active physical play
exhibiting strength and stamina.

BC338AA561344A518973BA5AFF6B0AE6.description:
Identify and describe the function
of body parts.

3961E3F757E74098AC7EC3D28C8535B7.description:
Regulate reactions to external
sensory stimuli in order to focus
on complex tasks or activities.

1B1F27349AAA4164BC052DD98B621996.description:
Demonstrate increasingly complex
oral-motor skills such as drinking
through a straw, blowing bubbles
or repeating a tongue-twister.

BAEA2CD42ABD4EA3B2655DE5DF9DC019.description:
Use classroom and household
tools independently with eye-hand
coordination to carry out activities.

A9D37245A4CC47B8905234AC5D25FBC8.description:
Coordinate the use of hands,
fingers and wrists to manipulate
objects and perform tasks requiring
precise movements

68EB5447D1FA46CB8076D2C63A9BC4BA.description: Small Muscle: Touch, Grasp, Reach, Manipulate

2116B2ECC9C84C0CB3D0000875C1D912.description:
Demonstrate spatial awareness in
physical activity or movement

4F1BE29ACA754EA1A0BECD7299E46B37.description:
Use non-locomotor skills with
control, balance and coordination
during active play (e.g., bending,
stretching and twisting).

14FEBD036B75445D8E5FD4ECDD8D81BB.description:
Demonstrate coordination in using
objects during active play (e.g.,
throwing, catching, kicking balls,
riding tricycle).

DC6384E0752041808442A64557945A11.description:
Demonstrate locomotor skills with
control, coordination and balance
during active play (e.g., running,
hopping, skipping).

E98AB0A1FA9241B590506AE13054B056.description:
Express interest in and show
appreciation for the creative work
of others.

F8BF6558C79B4B60B9201579E60F2B03.description:
Express individuality, life
experiences, and what they
know and are able to do
through a variety of media.

DA2226109E2141C8925F4A1563649F94.description: Expression of Ideas and Feelings Through the Arts

58BF59EDDB90476DBB3C5453AD1B4DD0.description:
Use creative and flexible thinking
to solve problems.

7AC7E0F34F1346D596AA4749D551D4FA.description:
Use imagination and creativity
to interact with objects and
materials.

A1E9301632484225A1B08EDA7EC64DFC.description:
Focus on the task at hand even
when frustrated or challenged.

2BBB6D922DFB457D89B6A9A446EED48C.description:
Carry out tasks, activities,
projects or experiences from
beginning to end.

68E068E99B8848168BFF175DDD2DFCB6.description:
Focus on an activity with
deliberate concentration
despite distractions.

95009C5C833A4D5D8C071DD412EFD4A7.description:
Use prior knowledge and
information to assess, inform, and
plan for future actions and learning.

ADC0729523994EC8BD685F80B513A99D.description:
Develop, initiate and carry out
simple plans to obtain a goal.

54F7CCE46AD04B7DB762812ED6AF8C42.description:
Ask questions to seek explanations
about phenomena of interest.

06A1A222A1D845F4B61CBE29F4FBB97B.description:
Demonstrate self-direction while
participating in a range of activities
and routines.

1DAD6358B65641009DD83D076D6A3C69.description:
Seek new and varied experiences
and challenges (takes risks).

E7B7452AAE70413F9EEC62C32C2F8708.description:
Show regard for the feelings of
other living things.

76B29454C7754D3E81E1D5BF2E22B70F.description:
Express concern for the needs of
others and people in distress.

C7BF97650BB240B2B13B8AD928D9A1BE.description:
With modeling and support,
negotiate to resolve social conflicts
with peers.

3E13AA585F0C41E090585CE26DE38715.description:
Demonstrate socially competent
behavior with peers.

F89A501929884B58B58512490924A52E.description:
Interact with peers in more
complex pretend play including
planning, coordination of roles
and cooperation.

E3C5387E6D6846279C2AF5FDA29E3BDE.description:
Request and accept guidance from
familiar adults.

5D8261E1E14B4E1BBC3C35F85AAAF636.description:
Engage in extended, reciprocal
conversations with familiar adults.

A451392574F84FACB55889C9B556D0BB.description:
Separate from familiar adults in
a familiar setting with minimal
distress.

097B90003BD748C9A47AE43E958B40DD.description:
Seek security and support from
familiar adults in anticipation of
challenging situations.

CED00EDB13254B378A27A672B122170C.description:
Show confidence in own abilities
and accomplish routine and familiar
tasks independently

7897B1AAFD4F413A80A0FCE551BE6B44.description:
With modeling and support, show
awareness of the consequences for
his/her actions.

6A1C1382838E4F1BA8ADF60ACC3E8DAD.description:
Demonstrate the ability to delay
gratification for short periods
of time.

16948DDB5BE8489D969778DA059DAF8F.description:
Manage the expression of feelings,
thoughts, impulses and behaviors
with minimal guidance from adults.

4FD6FE0A1AB443F19ED1D91BD1F2470C.description:
Compare own characteristics to
those of others

0F4A5AE0BE8C4160868075E7A13F18D4.description:
Identify the diversity in human
characteristics and how people
are similar and different.

1E141DF13DC74BF79C06F9536F3DDEC6.description:
Communicate a range of
emotions in socially accepted
ways.

BAE6EC4E85F04BB9AF23A6E3BE2D5B9D.description:
Recognize and identify own
emotions and the emotions
of others
